>
  <main id="main">
<header class="page-hero"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / The Society</div><span class="kicker">A civic home for service</span><h1>Belonging that endures beyond an appointment</h1><p>The Society honors service, convenes exceptional people, elevates public-interest work, and creates a lasting civic identity.</p></div></header>
<nav class="anchor-nav" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#overview">The Society</a><a href="#community">Cohorts & Chapters</a><a href="#convenings">Convenings & Honors</a><a href="#service">Code of Service</a><a href="#oath">The Oath</a><a href="#advisors">Advisors</a></div></nav>
<section class="section" id="overview"><div class="container"><div class="grid grid--2"><div class="prose"><span class="eyebrow">The Fellowship Society</span><h2>People joined by what they are willing to contribute</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>US Fellows is more than a program. The Society is the civic home of Fellows, advisors, alumni, Host Institutions, and mission partners.</p><p>It convenes people across disciplines and generations who share a commitment to public service, institutional strength, scientific progress, human dignity, and the future of civil society.</p></div><blockquote class="quote"><p>“Fellows serve missions, not ego. Fellows strengthen institutions, not merely themselves.”</p><cite>Code of Service</cite></blockquote></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--mist" id="community"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro section-intro--center"><span class="eyebrow">Society Life</span><h2>A national community across missions and generations</h2><div class="rule"></div></div><div class="grid grid--4"><article class="card"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="users" /></div><h3>Cohorts</h3><p>Fellows appointed in shared periods build relationships across disciplines and mission areas.</p></article><article class="card"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="map-marker" /></div><h3>Chapters</h3><p>Place-based communities bring Fellows and partners together around regional public needs.</p></article><article class="card"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="history" /></div><h3>Alumni</h3><p>A continuing fellowship identity sustains connection long after an appointment concludes.</p></article><article class="card"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="sitemap" /></div><h3>Council of Fellows</h3><p>Experienced members help carry standards, knowledge, and service across the Society.</p></article></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--navy" id="convenings"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Convenings & Honors</span><h2>Recognition in the company of service</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>The Society creates occasions to exchange knowledge, examine important missions, recognize contribution, and strengthen relationships among Fellows and institutions.</p></div><div class="grid grid--3"><article class="number-card"><span class="number-card__num">Convene</span><h3>Mission gatherings</h3><p>Cross-disciplinary conversations centered on questions of public consequence.</p></article><article class="number-card"><span class="number-card__num">Recognize</span><h3>Awards and honors</h3><p>Distinctions that elevate serious work and meaningful contribution.</p></article><article class="number-card"><span class="number-card__num">Connect</span><h3>Institutional exchange</h3><p>Relationships among Fellows, advisors, hosts, and mission partners.</p></article></div></div></section>
<section class="section" id="service"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Code of Service</span><h2>The conduct expected of a US Fellow</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Fellows are expected to act with integrity, humility, excellence, discipline, respect, and commitment to the public good.</p></div><div class="program-grid program-grid--3"><article class="program"><h3>Integrity</h3><p>Be honest, responsible, and worthy of the trust placed in the fellowship.</p></article><article class="program"><h3>Humility</h3><p>Listen, learn, and place mission above personal recognition.</p></article><article class="program"><h3>Excellence</h3><p>Bring rigor and discipline to every contribution.</p></article><article class="program"><h3>Respect</h3><p>Honor the people, communities, and institutions affected by the work.</p></article><article class="program"><h3>Stewardship</h3><p>Leave institutions stronger and knowledge more useful.</p></article><article class="program"><h3>Public Good</h3><p>Judge success by the benefit created beyond oneself.</p></article></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--blue" id="oath"><div class="container oath"><span class="eyebrow">The Fellowship Oath</span><p>I accept the honor of fellowship in service to humanity, civil society, science, and the nation.</p><p>I will contribute my knowledge, discipline, imagination, and effort to missions larger than myself.</p><p>I will use my fellowship not merely as a distinction, but as a commitment.</p></div></section>
<section class="section" id="advisors"><div class="container"><div class="grid grid--2"><div><span class="eyebrow">Advisors</span><h2>Experience placed in service to others</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>US Fellows Advisors offer guidance, mentorship, institutional knowledge, subject-matter expertise, and mission counsel to Fellows and Host Institutions.</p></div><div class="cta" style="padding:42px"><div><h2 style="font-size:2.35rem">Join as an Advisor</h2><p>Scholars, executives, public servants, researchers, nonprofit leaders, scientists, educators, and experienced professionals are invited to express interest.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="fellowship-society.html">Learn More</a></div></div></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--mist"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">A society that stays useful</span><h2>Belonging continues after an appointment</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>The Society is designed to preserve relationships and public-purpose identity beyond one project. Its value grows when Fellows continue to exchange knowledge, mentor others, identify new missions, and help institutions learn.</p></div><div class="grid grid--3"><article class="card"><h3>Peer exchange</h3><p>Fellows bring different disciplines and regional perspectives to difficult questions without expecting one field to supply every answer.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Institutional memory</h3><p>Hosts, advisors, and alumni carry practical lessons forward so future appointments can begin with more context and stronger judgment.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Renewed service</h3><p>Society participation creates routes to advise, convene, publish, mentor, or contribute again as needs and capabilities change.</p></article></div><p class="section-note"><strong>Membership as practice:</strong> The Society is strongest when its name describes an active network of responsibility rather than a passive roster.</p></div></section>
</main>

</BaseLayout>
